Lineamientos

Parametrizacion

1. Overview of Changes

1.1. URL

The domain will be changed. Any references to

“https://portal.runmyprocess.com/"

must be changed to

"https://portal.aw1.us.runmyprocess.com/".

Application ID and version ID of applications will not be changed.

1.2. IP address

The IP address of the RMP servers will change. If corporate firewalls are filtering traffic, the

firewalls will need to be updated with the new IP addresses for RMP servers.

1.3. Endpoint

1.3.1. SEC

Before migration:

https://sdc.runmyprocess.com:4433/

After migration:

https://sdc.aw1.us.runmyprocess.com:4433/

1.3.2. SAML (Assertion Consumer Service)

Before migration:

https://live.runmyprocess.com/saml/acs

Entity ID: runmyprocess.jp

After migration:

https://live.aw1.us.runmyprocess.com/saml/acs

Entity ID: aw1.us.runmyprocess.com

1.3.3. Email

Before migration:

no-reply@runmyprocess.com

After migration:

no-reply@aw1.us.runmyprocess.com

1.3.4. Process Launcher

Email address to launch a process.

Before migration:

process+{ACCOUNT_ID}.{PROCESS_ID}@runmyprocess.com

After migration:

process+{ACCOUNT_ID}.{PROCESS_ID}@aw1.us.runmyprocess.com


2. Migration Limitations

● Usage data (e.g. number of process execution) is out of migration scope.

● Logs on "Logs Application" is out of migration scope.

3. Migration Preparation

3.1. Applications

It is highly recommended that wherever possible within an application, use parameterized URLs

rather than hard coded URLs. All RMP internal variables are defined here and section 1 defines

the specific parameters for URLs.

For example, if a resource uses this URL:

https://live.runmyprocess.com

the resource should be rewritten to use this:

${P_urls.live})

Doing so will ensure that there will be no migration issues.

For each and every application, in each resource shown below, scan all hard-coded values,

Javascript and Freemarker for hard coded URLs or dynamically constructed URLs.

Av. Cerro de las Torres 395, Col. Campestre Churubusco, C.P. 04200, Ciudad de México
